               <head>Extracts on Afghanistan</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary/>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85064939 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85001521 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85011394 http://lccn.loc.gov/n86066493" n="1" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_3770-item1">
                     <note>
                        <p>Miscellaneous extracts and tracts in Persian relating to the history of Afghanistan, also covering Baluchistan, parts of which are attibuted to the scribe, Yaḥyá Munshīʾ</p>
                        <p>Some variation in dimentions of individual tracts </p>
                        <p>Annotations in English, possibly by Anderson </p>
                        <p>List of contents in English (f. 244v), possibly by Anderson </p>
                        <p>IOL stamp: 19 Mar 1909
</p>
                        <p>Watermarks: 1) ФKHL (f. 192); 2) VIGO (f. 226); 3) erect bear with axe in ornamented oval frame (f. 228)</p>
                        <p>Not dated</p>
                        <p>Rare treatise with graphic diagrams (ff. 228v-242v) on coins excavated from Kandahar, entitled <title>Z̤arb al-buldān</title> and composed by Mīrzā Ḥasan ʿAlī Hiravī for the master of Shāh Shujāʿ al-Mulk's cannonade (tūp khānah), Andarsan Ṣāḥib. Prefixed with a note in English (f. 228r): <q>Transcripts of a few coins found at Kundahar copied by Husun Alee, 1844</q>.
                        </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="eng">Persian &amp; English</textLang>
                  </msItem>
